<p>Dear Sir,</p>
<p><strong><u>Subject: Change in Legal Name and Bank Account.</u></strong></p>
<p>We, <strong>{!accObj.Legal_Name__c}</strong> (formerly known as <strong>{!accParentObj.Legal_Name__c}</strong>) a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 2013, entered into a services agreement/ an agreement vide an account opening form dated <strong><apex:outputText value="{0,date,MM'/'dd'/'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!TODAY()}" /></apex:outputText>("Service Agreement")</strong> with PayU Payments Private Limited <strong>("PayU")</strong>, in accordance to which PayU provides us with aggregate online payment gateway solutions and services through its PayU platform <strong>("PayU Services")</strong> for our website with domain name: <strong>{!oppObj.Website__c}</strong></p>
<p>This letter is to inform PayU that our legal name has changed from</p>
<p><strong>{!accParentObj.Legal_Name__c}</strong></p>
<p>To</p>
<p><strong>{!accObj.Legal_Name__c}</strong></p>
<p>In this respect, we request PayU to make the requisite change to the Service Agreement and such other documents as required in order to avail the PayU Services.</p>
<p>We understands that the submission of this letter will constitute as an amendment to the Service Agreement and hereby confirm that there has been no change in the constitution, management, registered address of <strong>{!accParentObj.Legal_Name__c}</strong>, and/or the Authorized Signatory since the last application submitted to PayU.</p>
<p>In addition, We would like to change our Merchant Account (as defined in the Service Agreement), in which the Customer Charge minus the TDR ("Settlement Amount") payable to us, is settled by PayU under the Service Agreement.</p>
<br/>
